<page>
<title>True / False</title>
<problem>
    <introduction>
        <p>
            (8 points) Suppose <m>A</m> is an <m>m \times n</m> matrix and <m>\vec b\in \mathbb R ^{m}</m> unless otherwise stated. Select <em>true</em> if the statement is true for all choices of <m>A</m> and <m>\vec b</m>.  Otherwise, select <em>false</em>.
        </p>
    </introduction>
    <task workspace="true">
    <statement>
        <p>
            <em>True &#160;  / &#160;  False</em>: &#160; There are infinity many invertible matrices <m> A </m> satisfying <m> A^2 = A</m>.  
        </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
            False.
        </p>
    </answer>
    <solution>
        <p>
            Solution text
        </p>
        <p>
            Counterexample: 
        </p>
    </solution>
    </task>

    <task workspace="true">
        <statement>
            <p>
                <em>True &#160;  / &#160;  False</em>: &#160; If <m>A</m> and <m> B </m> are invertible matrices, then <m> A + B </m> is also invertible.
            </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
            <p>
                False.
            </p>
        </answer>
        <solution>
            <p>
                Solution text
            </p>    
            <p>    
                Counterexample: 
            </p>
        </solution>
    </task>

    <task workspace="true">
        <statement>
            <p>
                <em>True &#160;  / &#160;  False</em>: &#160; If the matrix product <m> AB </m> is defined, then <m>BA</m> is also defined.
            </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
            <p>
                False
            </p>
        </answer>
        <solution>
            <p>
                Solution text
            </p>
        </solution>
    </task>

    <task workspace="true">
        <statement>
            <p>
                <em>True &#160;  / &#160;  False</em>: &#160; If <m> A </m> is an <m> n \times m </m> matrix and <m> AB </m> is an <m>n \times r </m> matrix, then <m>B</m> has <m>r</m> columns.
            </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
            <p>
                True.
            </p>
        </answer>
        <solution>
            <p>
                Solution text
            </p>
            <p>
                Counterexample
            </p>
        </solution>
    </task>

    
</problem>


</page>


<page>
<problem>
    <introduction>
        <p>
           (4 points) Indicate whether the following situations are possible or impossible. 
        </p>
    </introduction>
    <task workspace="0.5in">
        <statement>
            <p>
                <em>Possible &#160;  / &#160;  Impossible</em>: &#160; An invertible matrix with a unique <m> LU </m> factorization.
            </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
            <p>
                Possible.
            </p>
        </answer>
        <solution>
            <p>
                Solution Text
            </p>
        </solution>
    </task>

    <task workspace="0.5in">
        <statement>
            <p>
                <em>Possible &#160;  / &#160;  Impossible</em>: &#160; Two matrices <m>A</m> and <m>B</m> such that <m>(A + B)^2 = A^2 +B^2 + 2AB</m>.
            </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
            <p>
                Possible.
            </p>
        </answer>
        <solution>
            <p>
                Solution Text. (A=B= zero matrix should work)
            </p>
        </solution>
    </task>


</problem>

<p workspace="0.5in">
    
</p>

<problem workspace="3in">
    <statement>
        <p>        
            (2 points) Multiple Choice Problem: Select all that apply or Select only one. Let <m>A</m> be an <m>n \times n</m> matrix such that for every <m>\vec{b} \in \mathbb{R}^n</m>, the system <m>A \vec{x} = \vec{b}</m> has a unique solution.

        </p>
        
        <ol marker="(a)">
            <li><m>A</m> has a pivot in each column.</li>
            <li>dim <m>\{ \vec{x} | A \vec{x} = \vec{0} \} > 0</m>.</li>
            <li><m>A^T \vec{x} = \vec{b}</m> has a unique solution.</li>
            <li>The columns of <m>A</m> span <m>\mathbb{R}^n</m>.</li>
        </ol>

    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
            Options (a), (c), and (d) are correct
        </p>
    </answer>
    <solution>
        <p>
            Option (a) is correct.
        </p>
        <p>
            Option (b) is incorrect.
        </p>
        <p>
            Option (c) is correct.
        </p>
        <p>
            Option (d) is correct.
        </p>
    </solution>
</problem>
    
</page>

<page>
    <problem workspace="true">
        <statement>
            <p>
                (3 points) Let <m>A</m> be a <m>3 \times 4</m> matrix. Let 
                <me> D = \begin{pmatrix}A \amp B \\ C \amp I_5 \end{pmatrix}</me>

                Find the dimension of matrices <m>B, C, </m> and <m>D</m>:

                <me>B \text{ has _______}  \text{ rows and _______}  \text{ columns}</me>
                <me>C \text{ has _______}  \text{ rows and _______}  \text{ columns}</me>
                <me>D \text{ has _______}  \text{ rows and _______}  \text{ columns}</me>

            </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
            <p>
                <m>B</m> has 3 rows and 5 columns. <m>C</m> has 5 rows and 4 columns. <m>D</m> has 8 rows and 9 columns.
            </p>
        </answer>
        <solution>
            <p>
                Solution text for B
            </p>
            <p>
                Solution text for C
            </p>
            <p>
                Solution text for D
            </p>
        </solution>
    </problem>

    <problem workspace="true">
        <statement>
            <p>    
                Let <m>A = \begin{pmatrix} a \amp 0 \\ b \amp 1 \end{pmatrix}</m> and <m>AA^T = I_2</m>. Find all possible values for <m>a</m> and <m>b</m>.


                <me>a = \framebox{$\phantom{$\begin{bmatrix} a \amp a \amp a \amp a \amp a \end{bmatrix}$}$ } </me>
                <me>b = \framebox{$\phantom{$\begin{bmatrix} a \amp a \amp a \amp a \amp a \end{bmatrix}$}$ } </me>
            </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
            <p>
                <m>a = \pm 1</m> and <m>b = 0</m>.
            </p>
        </answer>
        <solution>
            <p>
                Solution text
            </p>
        </solution>
    </problem>

    <problem workspace="1.5in">
        <statement>
            <p>
                Let <m>A = \begin{pmatrix}1 \amp 3 \\ 0 \amp 1\end{pmatrix}</m>. Find <m>A^{500}</m>. <m>\textit{Hint: First compute $A^2$, then $A^3$, and continue computing successive powers until you recognize a pattern.}</m>
            </p>
            <p>
                <me>A^{500} = \framebox{$\phantom{$\begin{bmatrix} a \amp a \amp a \amp a \amp a \\ b  \\ c \\d \\ d \\ d \end{bmatrix}$}$ } </me>
                
            </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
            <p>
                <m>A^{500} = \begin{bmatrix} 1 \amp 1500 \\ 0 \amp 1 \end{bmatrix}</m>
            </p>
        </answer>
        <solution>
            <p>
                Solution text 
            </p>
        </solution>
    </problem>
</page>

<page>
    

    <problem workspace="2in">
        <introduction>
            <p>
                Show your work problem. Part of the grade is based on the justification/ work shown. Can have parts. E.g.
            </p>
        </introduction>
        <statement>
            <p>
                (5 points) Show your work in the space below and put your answer in the boxes.

                Let 
                
                <me>
                        A = \begin{pmatrix} 1 \amp 2 \amp 3 \\ 0 \amp 1 \amp 4 \\ 0 \amp 0 \amp 1 \end{pmatrix}, \vec{b} = \begin{pmatrix} 6 \\ 5 \\ 3 \end{pmatrix}
                    </me>
            </p>
            <p>
                (a) Form the augmented matrix <m>[A | I_3] </m>

            <me>[A|I_3] =  \framebox{$\phantom{$\begin{bmatrix} a \amp a \amp a \amp a \amp a \amp a \amp a \\ b  \\ c \\d \\ d \\ d \amp d \ amp d \end{bmatrix}$}$ } </me>
            </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
            <p>
                <m>[A | I_3] =     \left[\begin{array}{ccc|ccc}
    1 \amp 2 \amp 3 \amp 1 \amp 0 \amp 0 \\
    0 \amp 1 \amp 4 \amp 0 \amp 1 \amp 0 \\
    0 \amp 0 \amp 1 \amp 0 \amp 0 \amp 1
    \end{array}\right].</m>
            </p>
        </answer>
        <solution>
            <p>
                Solution text
            </p>
        </solution>

        <statement>
            (b) Use elementary row operations to reduce <m> [A|I_3]</m> to <m> [I_3|B]</m>

            <me>[I_3|B] = \framebox{$\phantom{$\begin{bmatrix} a \amp a \amp a \amp a \amp a \amp a \amp a \\ b  \\ c \\d \\ d \\ d \amp d \ amp d \end{bmatrix}$}$ }</me>
        </statement>

        <answer>
            <p>
                <m>[A | I_3] =     \left[\begin{array}{ccc|ccc}
    1 \amp 0 \amp 0 \amp 1 \amp -2 \amp 5 \\
    0 \amp 1 \amp 0 \amp 0 \amp 1 \amp -4 \\
    0 \amp 0 \amp 1 \amp 0 \amp 0 \amp 1
    \end{array}\right].</m>
            </p>
        </answer>
        <solution>
            <p>
                Solution text
            </p>
        </solution>

        <statement>
            (C) What is the relationship between <m>B</m> and <m>A</m>

            <me>\framebox{$\phantom{$\begin{bmatrix} a \amp a \amp a \amp a \end{bmatrix}$}$ }</me>
        </statement>

        <answer>
            <p>
                <m>B = A^{-1}</m>
            </p>
        </answer>
        <solution>
            <p>
                Solution text
            </p>
        </solution>


    </problem>




</page>
    
